<br>
This weekend I buckled down and gave charm-soloing another shot. The major reason is that I've been playing my mage a lot when I don't have much time to devote to a group, can't find a group, etc. ... and the mage has been getting way too much playtime.<br>
<br>
Anyway, as fate would have it I was in Dreadlands. At level 42 with 170 charisma, the cockatrices and drolvargs held charm pretty consistently. I didn't spend hours and hours doing this, but in the time I spent there I only had one early charm break, which was unusual (but in a good way). Mobs were pretty scarce though, and I remembered that rhinos in Overthere were fairly slow-moving, so I went there. Well, I found out that I was wrong ... the rhinos, though they do make great pets, are very upset once they come to their senses. And they run every bit as fast as jboots while pounding on your backside. In contrast, the cockatrices and drolvargs were easily outpaced with jboots.<br>
<br>
So here comes the meat of my question ... where are there other relatively slow-moving mobs that are conducive to charming? I would stick with Dreadlands, but got Velious for xmas and am going to try some of the mobs there, but just in case that doesn't work out, I'd like some other options ... say, in case I can't get a ride back to Dreadlands (I have had way too much boat travel recently).<br>
<br>
Thanks, and happy chanting! <p><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

